# ============================================
# FRONTEND CONFIGURATION
# ============================================

# Backend API base URL
# Point this at the backend origin (not /api path)
# Development: http://localhost:3000
# Production: https://api.yourdomain.com
VITE_API_URL="http://localhost:3000"

# ============================================
# LIVE STREAMING (LiveKit)
# ============================================

# LiveKit WebSocket URL (optional)
# The frontend gets this from backend API responses at runtime
# This variable is kept for compatibility with existing deploy scripts
# Format: wss://your-project.livekit.cloud
VITE_LIVEKIT_WS_URL="wss://your-project.livekit.cloud"

# ============================================
# NOTES
# ============================================

# Development Setup:
# 1. Copy this file to .env
# 2. Update VITE_API_URL to match your backend URL
# 3. Run: bun install
# 4. Start dev server: bun run dev (runs on http://localhost:5173)

# Production Setup:
# - Set VITE_API_URL to production backend URL (must use HTTPS)
# - Ensure backend CORS allows frontend origin
# - Build for production: bun run build
# - Preview build: bun run preview
# - Deploy dist/ folder to CDN or static hosting

# Features:
# - User authentication (email/password, OTP, OAuth)
# - Live streaming (creator and viewer modes)
# - Social features (follow, like, comment, share)
# - Content feed (posts, shorts, videos)
# - Virtual gifts and coin purchases
# - Creator applications
# - Profile management
# - Search and discovery

# Environment Variables:
# - All VITE_ prefixed variables are exposed to the browser
# - Never put sensitive secrets in frontend .env files
# - Backend handles all sensitive operations (payments, auth, etc.)
